# Changelog

All notable changes to VOID STRIKER are documented here.
Format follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).
Versioning follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

---

## [Unreleased]

### Planned
- Co-op local multiplayer (split keyboard)
- Unlockable ship skins
- Daily challenge mode with seeded wave patterns
- Cloud leaderboard via optional backend

---

## [1.3.0] — 2025-06-01

### Added
- **Boss system** (`boss.js`) — every 5th wave now spawns a multi-phase boss with
  spread, laser, and aimed-burst attacks; damage phases change color and aggression.
- **Upgrade shop** (`shop.js`) — spend score between waves on fire rate, move speed,
  bullet damage, shield recharge, spread-shot unlock, and score boost.
- **Audio engine** (`audio.js`) — Web Audio API sound layer with procedural laser,
  explosion, power-up, and boss sounds; mute toggle persists via localStorage.
- **Stats tracker** (`stats.js`) — per-session and all-time stat tracking (kills,
  playtime, nukes, perfect waves, etc.) with a new Stats tab in the post-game overlay.
- `assets/` directory with logo, favicon, gameplay GIF, three screenshots, and four
  WAV sound effects.

### Changed
- Wave difficulty curve steepened at waves 8–10; enemy count capped at 45.
- Power-up spawn interval now scales more aggressively (floor lowered to 180 frames).
- `hitsOnWave1` achievement check is now correctly reset per run.

### Fixed
- Touch controls occasionally toggled `touchShoot` on fast swipes — now guarded with
  a minimum horizontal-movement threshold.
- Score multiplier was not applied to nuke kills.
- Spread-shot bullets could clip through the canvas left edge at extreme player positions.

---

## [1.2.1] — 2025-04-18

### Fixed
- `localStorage` JSON parse error on corrupted leaderboard entries no longer crashes
  the game; entries are silently reset.
- Achievement toast could stack multiple times on rapid fire-rate triggers.

---

## [1.2.0] — 2025-03-30

### Added
- 12 achievements with toast notifications and persistent unlock state.
- `UNTOUCHABLE` achievement: complete wave 1 without being hit.
- `LIGHTNING PILOT` achievement: clear wave 3 in under 30 seconds.
- Leaderboard now stores pilot name (up to 8 characters), score, and wave reached.
- Mobile touch controls: tap left/right thirds to move, centre to shoot.

### Changed
- Enemy `tank` type now has 3 HP and a purple tint; worth 50 points.
- Power-up glow radius increased for better visibility on small screens.
- Overlay tabs (SCORES / ACHIEVEMENTS) replace the single post-game screen.

### Fixed
- `fast` enemy type could spawn on wave 1 under certain wave-count calculations.
- Spread-shot power-up was not correctly expiring after its duration.

---

## [1.1.0] — 2025-02-14

### Added
- Five power-up types: Shield (+1 life), Rapid Fire, Spread Shot, Nuke, Time Slow.
- Active-effect HUD bars showing remaining duration.
- Float text feedback when a power-up is collected.
- Enemy bullet variance by type (`fast` enemies shoot more often).

### Changed
- Star-field density increased to 120 stars; scroll speed now varies per star.
- Score displayed with `toLocaleString()` thousands separators.

---

## [1.0.0] — 2025-01-01

### Added
- Initial release: canvas-based space shooter with infinite wave progression.
- Three enemy types: basic, fast, tank.
- Player ship with keyboard (← → / A D + Space) and basic touch support.
- Local hi-score persistence via `localStorage`.
- Particle explosion system.
- 3-lives system with invincibility frames after taking damage.
- Responsive canvas capped at 480 × 560 px.

